            "answer_text": "Flash vaporisation occurs because at the reduced pressure the boiling point of the liquid becomes equal to or less than that of its actual temperature.  For the vapors to form, latent heat is required, which is extracted from the remaining liquid. So subsequently the temperature of the liquid falls below its boiling point at that pressure. That is the reason why  the entire liquid doesn't evaporate. ",
